headline.main: Text of Mayor LaGuardia's Six=Months' Report

docs.snippet: Following is the text of Mayor LaGuardia's report to the people of the City of New York on the work of his administration during its first six months:

docs.lead_paragraph: THE brief stories presented herewith constitute the midyear report of the Hundred Neediest Cases Fund. They tell of the progress made in six months by the 100 cases published by THE NEW YORK TIMES in its twenty-second annual appeal, on Dec. 3, last.

headline.main: THE NEEDIEST NO LONGER! SIX MONTHS OF PROGRESS; The Fund Given Last Christmas by Readers of The New York Times Is Rebuilding the Lives of Many Persons Who Were in Want THE STORIES OF THE TRANSFORMATION OF THE NEEDIEST A Midyear Account of the Gains Toward Self-Support That Have Been Made by Those Who at Christmas Were in Direst Distress
